TOKEN and CLIENT_ID diye rakci toke ogula add kore just eta run korish node src/index.js

Discord Bot Setup
Prerequisites

Install the following software:

Node.js (LTS version)
npm (installed with Node.js)
A Discord account
A Discord server where the bot can be invited

Verify installation:

node -v
npm -v
Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone <repository-url>
cd discord-bot

Install dependencies:

npm install
Discord Bot Configuration

Create a Discord application:

Go to https://discord.com/developers/applications
Click New Application
Give it a name
Go to Bot
Click Add Bot
Copy the Bot Token

Create a .env file in the project root.

Example:

TOKEN=YOUR_DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN
CLIENT_ID=YOUR_CLIENT_ID
API_URL=http://localhost:5000

Replace the values with your own.

Enable Required Intents

In the Discord Developer Portal:

Application
    ↓
Bot
    ↓
Privileged Gateway Intents

Enable:

Message Content Intent

Save the changes.

Invite the Bot

In the Discord Developer Portal:

OAuth2
    ↓
URL Generator

Select:

Scopes

bot

Permissions

View Channels
Send Messages
Read Message History

Open the generated URL and invite the bot to your Discord server.

Running the Bot

Start the bot:

node src/index.js

If everything is configured correctly, you should see:

IUT_Hackathon#1970 is online
Available Commands
!status

Shows the overall status of devices.

!room <room_name>

Shows the status of a specific room.

Example:

!room drawing
!usage

Shows current power usage statistics.

Backend Integration

Currently the bot uses mock data.

To connect to the backend:

Start the backend server.
Update the API_URL in the .env file.
Replace the mock implementation in:
src/services/api.js

with the actual API endpoints.

No changes are required in the command files.

Project Structure
discord-bot/
│
├── src/
│   ├── commands/
│   ├── services/
